{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/articles/thunderbolt-external-hard-drive-with-seagate-stae128-adapter","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"f9af0d7d-2a99-5206-b36c-310fb058b366","html":"<p>Yes, you can use the Seagate STAE128 Thunderbolt Adapter for Backup Plus with <strong>any</strong> SATA external 2.5” Hard Drive. You can also use the STAE121 but I’ve read that they discontinued that for the newer STAE128.</p>\n<p>Here’s a little review on my experience with the Seagate STAE128 Thunderbolt Adapter and a bare 2.5” SATA external hard drive. Since switching over to the Macbook Pro Retina with 256gb SSD, I’ve been a little worried about my hard drive space.</p>\n<p>Coming from the regular Macbook Pro with a 750gb hard drive I wasn’t used to worrying about space. I had to move all of my music to an external and reduced the amount of photos I could work on at a time. Since I scan my photos to raw uncompressed TIFF files at a fairly high DPI, the files are quite large. I used to keep about six months to a years worth of scanned negatives on my laptop at a time, and moved anything older to an external. With only 256gb to spare I’m limited to maybe half of that.</p>\n<p>So my research started when I was looking into an external in which I could use to edit directly on and was portable. This required something fast and small. I looked into USB 3.0 and Thunderbolt, to which the later provided minimal results. The best I could find were 3 or 4 heavy options for Thunderbolt external hard drives at really steep prices, considering I could buy a 1TB USB 3.0 portal external for a hundred dollars.</p>\n<p>After more research I came upon the Seagate Thunder Bolt Adapter, STAE 121, that would allow me to convert the Seagate enclosed external drives to Thunderbolt. A little more googling and I found out I could actually use the STAE 121 with a bare 2.5” SATA hard drive. A little skeptical at first mostly because of the lack of people talking about it on the internet, I went to Best Buy to see if they had it in stock.</p>\n<p>When I got there I found the newer version, the Seagate Thunderbolt Adapter <em>For Backup Plus</em>, or STAE128. A little confused, I tried to google it but found nothing. I bought it, and a Thunderbolt plug by Apple.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 600px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/159883599976a5dec79444da6c5d18c1/b4294/1.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/159883599976a5dec79444da6c5d18c1/8ac56/1.webp 240w,\n/static/159883599976a5dec79444da6c5d18c1/d3be9/1.webp 480w,\n/static/159883599976a5dec79444da6c5d18c1/e88ff/1.webp 600w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/159883599976a5dec79444da6c5d18c1/09b79/1.jpg 240w,\n/static/159883599976a5dec79444da6c5d18c1/7cc5e/1.jpg 480w,\n/static/159883599976a5dec79444da6c5d18c1/b4294/1.jpg 600w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/159883599976a5dec79444da6c5d18c1/b4294/1.jpg\"\n          alt=\"STAE 128 Seagate Thunderbolt Adapter for Backup Plus\"\n          title=\"STAE 128 Seagate Thunderbolt Adapter for Backup Plus\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 600px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/b4d98880fb460e16a0459431c7850cae/b4294/2.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/b4d98880fb460e16a0459431c7850cae/8ac56/2.webp 240w,\n/static/b4d98880fb460e16a0459431c7850cae/d3be9/2.webp 480w,\n/static/b4d98880fb460e16a0459431c7850cae/e88ff/2.webp 600w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/b4d98880fb460e16a0459431c7850cae/09b79/2.jpg 240w,\n/static/b4d98880fb460e16a0459431c7850cae/7cc5e/2.jpg 480w,\n/static/b4d98880fb460e16a0459431c7850cae/b4294/2.jpg 600w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/b4d98880fb460e16a0459431c7850cae/b4294/2.jpg\"\n          alt=\"STAE 128 Seagate Thunderbolt Adapter for Backup Plus\"\n          title=\"STAE 128 Seagate Thunderbolt Adapter for Backup Plus\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>At first I thought I would need to use a SATA cable to connect my hard drive, but it actually plugged right into it.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 600px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/2b130db42ebe9f811142c6839c200dfe/b4294/3.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/2b130db42ebe9f811142c6839c200dfe/8ac56/3.webp 240w,\n/static/2b130db42ebe9f811142c6839c200dfe/d3be9/3.webp 480w,\n/static/2b130db42ebe9f811142c6839c200dfe/e88ff/3.webp 600w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/2b130db42ebe9f811142c6839c200dfe/09b79/3.jpg 240w,\n/static/2b130db42ebe9f811142c6839c200dfe/7cc5e/3.jpg 480w,\n/static/2b130db42ebe9f811142c6839c200dfe/b4294/3.jpg 600w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/2b130db42ebe9f811142c6839c200dfe/b4294/3.jpg\"\n          alt=\"STAE 128 Seagate Thunderbolt Adapter for Backup Plus\"\n          title=\"STAE 128 Seagate Thunderbolt Adapter for Backup Plus\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 600px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/87d83890c8a54ea5e22dadc69c1e60ec/b4294/4.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/87d83890c8a54ea5e22dadc69c1e60ec/8ac56/4.webp 240w,\n/static/87d83890c8a54ea5e22dadc69c1e60ec/d3be9/4.webp 480w,\n/static/87d83890c8a54ea5e22dadc69c1e60ec/e88ff/4.webp 600w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/87d83890c8a54ea5e22dadc69c1e60ec/09b79/4.jpg 240w,\n/static/87d83890c8a54ea5e22dadc69c1e60ec/7cc5e/4.jpg 480w,\n/static/87d83890c8a54ea5e22dadc69c1e60ec/b4294/4.jpg 600w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/87d83890c8a54ea5e22dadc69c1e60ec/b4294/4.jpg\"\n          alt=\"STAE 128 Seagate Thunderbolt Adapter for Backup Plus\"\n          title=\"STAE 128 Seagate Thunderbolt Adapter for Backup Plus\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 600px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/934179d8b1e4fd62b7d4026834b5f6f0/b4294/5.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/934179d8b1e4fd62b7d4026834b5f6f0/8ac56/5.webp 240w,\n/static/934179d8b1e4fd62b7d4026834b5f6f0/d3be9/5.webp 480w,\n/static/934179d8b1e4fd62b7d4026834b5f6f0/e88ff/5.webp 600w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/934179d8b1e4fd62b7d4026834b5f6f0/09b79/5.jpg 240w,\n/static/934179d8b1e4fd62b7d4026834b5f6f0/7cc5e/5.jpg 480w,\n/static/934179d8b1e4fd62b7d4026834b5f6f0/b4294/5.jpg 600w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/934179d8b1e4fd62b7d4026834b5f6f0/b4294/5.jpg\"\n          alt=\"STAE 128 Seagate Thunderbolt Adapter for Backup Plus\"\n          title=\"STAE 128 Seagate Thunderbolt Adapter for Backup Plus\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>I’m using a Seagate Momentus 7200rpm 500gb hard drive which I pulled from my old Macbook Pro. I don’t have any benchmarks from when that was installed internally, but I did find a few through google and this seems to be about the average.</p>\n<p>My results using the same hard drive and the Seagate Thunderbolt Adapter STAE128 were very close to that.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 500px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/21675ca16bc4122d444311c77b278d66/0b533/6.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 62.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/21675ca16bc4122d444311c77b278d66/8ac56/6.webp 240w,\n/static/21675ca16bc4122d444311c77b278d66/d3be9/6.webp 480w,\n/static/21675ca16bc4122d444311c77b278d66/b0a15/6.webp 500w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/21675ca16bc4122d444311c77b278d66/8ff5a/6.png 240w,\n/static/21675ca16bc4122d444311c77b278d66/e85cb/6.png 480w,\n/static/21675ca16bc4122d444311c77b278d66/0b533/6.png 500w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/21675ca16bc4122d444311c77b278d66/0b533/6.png\"\n          alt=\"Seagate Thunderbolt Adapter for Backup Plus STAE128 Benchmark\"\n          title=\"Seagate Thunderbolt Adapter for Backup Plus STAE128 Benchmark\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Compared to my 2TB Western Digital External HDD USB2.0.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 500px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/122289d0a38a4bccac0568db7356415c/0b533/7.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 60.416666666666664%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/122289d0a38a4bccac0568db7356415c/8ac56/7.webp 240w,\n/static/122289d0a38a4bccac0568db7356415c/d3be9/7.webp 480w,\n/static/122289d0a38a4bccac0568db7356415c/b0a15/7.webp 500w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/122289d0a38a4bccac0568db7356415c/8ff5a/7.png 240w,\n/static/122289d0a38a4bccac0568db7356415c/e85cb/7.png 480w,\n/static/122289d0a38a4bccac0568db7356415c/0b533/7.png 500w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/122289d0a38a4bccac0568db7356415c/0b533/7.png\"\n          alt=\"Compare\"\n          title=\"Compare\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>and for fun, compared to the internal 256gb SSD that’s inside my Macbook Retina.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 500px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/47b3addb71a8f56eb8218e479d061ebe/0b533/8.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.33333333333333%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/47b3addb71a8f56eb8218e479d061ebe/8ac56/8.webp 240w,\n/static/47b3addb71a8f56eb8218e479d061ebe/d3be9/8.webp 480w,\n/static/47b3addb71a8f56eb8218e479d061ebe/b0a15/8.webp 500w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/47b3addb71a8f56eb8218e479d061ebe/8ff5a/8.png 240w,\n/static/47b3addb71a8f56eb8218e479d061ebe/e85cb/8.png 480w,\n/static/47b3addb71a8f56eb8218e479d061ebe/0b533/8.png 500w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/47b3addb71a8f56eb8218e479d061ebe/0b533/8.png\"\n          alt=\"Macbook Pro Retina 256gb SSD Benchmark\"\n          title=\"Macbook Pro Retina 256gb SSD Benchmark\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Overall I’m definitely happy with the STAE128. I get to use my SATA 2.5” hard drives that I have laying around, I get speeds that match internal speeds, it’s portable and self powered, and best of all it was only <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>99</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mo>+</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">99(+</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">9</span><span class=\"mord\">9</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\">+</span></span></span></span>50 for the Thunderbolt cable). The price alone beats any of the other Thunderbolt options out right now.</p>\n<p>Next up, installing and booting Windows 7 off the STAE128 Thunderbolt drive.</p>\n<p>UPDATE:</p>\n<p>I successfully installed, and am now running, Windows 7 from my Thunderbolt external hard drive. I followed <a href=\"https://forums.macrumors.com/threads/rmbp-bootcamp-off-thunderbolt-drive-more-complete-solution.1414769/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">these directions</a> and it worked perfectly.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 400px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/e6f101a52826d7b68c15ab1f20d901ad/066f9/windows_thunderbolt_benchmark.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 127.91666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/e6f101a52826d7b68c15ab1f20d901ad/8ac56/windows_thunderbolt_benchmark.webp 240w,\n/static/e6f101a52826d7b68c15ab1f20d901ad/7f61c/windows_thunderbolt_benchmark.webp 400w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/e6f101a52826d7b68c15ab1f20d901ad/09b79/windows_thunderbolt_benchmark.jpg 240w,\n/static/e6f101a52826d7b68c15ab1f20d901ad/066f9/windows_thunderbolt_benchmark.jpg 400w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/e6f101a52826d7b68c15ab1f20d901ad/066f9/windows_thunderbolt_benchmark.jpg\"\n          alt=\"Windows 7 Thunderbolt STAE128 benchmark\"\n          title=\"Windows 7 Thunderbolt STAE128 benchmark\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>","fields":{"slug":"/articles/thunderbolt-external-hard-drive-with-seagate-stae128-adapter","tagSlugs":["/tag/hardware/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2012-12-14","description":"Yes, you can use the Seagate STAE128 Thunderbolt Adapter for Backup Plus with any SATA external 2.5\" Hard Drive.","tags":["Hardware"],"title":"Thunderbolt External Hard Drive with Seagate STAE128 Adapter","legacyArticleId":"45"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/articles/thunderbolt-external-hard-drive-with-seagate-stae128-adapter"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2255556206","251939775","401334301"]}